(12, 'SUB0011', 'Principles of Management', 'principles-of-management', '', 'download2.png', '<p><strong>Principles of management assignment help</strong></p>\r\n<p>Management is a field of wide research and applications. Koontz defines management as an area which consists of getting the things done with the help of other people. A manager is the person who accomplishes the group aims by directing other people efforts.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Management actually is guiding physical and human resources into a very dynamic, hard-hitting business until that achieves its objectives to satisfaction of the people served, and with high degree of self-confidence and a sense of achievement on part of those people who are rendering the services.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../assets/images/album/images1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n<p>Urwick defines it as the great art of directing human’s activities. Management is thought of as the science and art of making decisions. It’s the process of using resources for accomplishment of goals. Many other views from people on management include:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>•         It is the procedure of getting the things done well- productivity, performance and prosperity wise.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>•         It is an art of coordinating available resources: men, material, machine, market, money, knowledge and even information.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>•         It is the procedure of planning staffing, organizing, influencing, controlling and leading people.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>•         It is a science and art of directing and organizing human efforts used to control forces as well as utilize the materials of nature for mankind benefits.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>•         Management is continuously coordinated activity using which any administration or any undertaking or any other services, private or public, conducts its own business.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>•         It is a form or process of work which involves the direction or guidance 