(217, 'SUB00212', 'Services Marketing ', 'services-marketing', '', 'download39.png', '<p> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/download23.jpg\" alt=\"\">Services Marketing</span></strong><span xss=removed> is a subject the purpose of which is to provide an in-depth appreciation and understanding of the unique challenges inherent in managing and delivering quality services. Through the course the students are introduced to tools and strategies that address the challenges, develop an understanding of the “<strong xss=removed>state of the art</strong>” <strong xss=removed>service management</strong> thinking and encourage to adopt a customer service-oriented mindset. Through the course students learn to evaluate the impact of services on the US and World economies and outline & understand the unique challenges posed in the marketing of services that are not typically experienced while marketing traditional products. In order to help students to understand this subject better and comfortably face the challenges posed by the subject, <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong>. These classes have been designed to assist students and are light so that students are able to manage these classes with regular classes.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>The various topic covered under our <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong> for <strong xss=removed>Service Marketing</strong> are <strong xss=removed>New Perspectives on Marketing in the Service Economy, Consumer Behaviour in a Services Context, Positioning Services in Competitive Markets, Developing Service Products: Core and Supplementary Elements, Distributing Services through Physical and Electronic Channel, Setting Prices and Implementing Revenue, Management, Promoting Services and Educating Customers, Designing and Managing Service Processes, Balancing Demand and Productive Capacity<span xss=removed>,</span> Crafting the Service Environment, Managing People for Service Advantage, Managing Relationships and Building Loyalty, Complaint Handling and Service Recovery, Improving Service Quality and Productivity, Striving for Service Leadership</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions’</strong> online classes have been designed by a panel of experts who aren’t just highly qualified but also hold valuable teaching experience in Management. The classes have been designed while keeping students’ interest in mind. The <strong xss=removed>online classes help </strong>are distributed over a few weeks so that the course can be studied along with regular classes and is easy to grasp. If you wish to take <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions’ online classes help</strong> for <strong xss=removed>Services Marketing 4123 </strong>then you can contact us via E-mail or phone call. You can also hit the Take my online classes tab in the home page of our website for details.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n<p> </p>', 'COS0072', NULL, NULL),
(218, 'SUB00213', 'Sports Marketing ', 'sports-marketing', '', 'images18.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed>Sports Marketing</span></strong><span xss=removed> is a stream of marketing that focusses on the marketing of sports. When it comes to marketing a sport, the <strong xss=removed>marketing strategies and fundamentals</strong> vary. They are different from the marketing strategies used for promoting businesses in general. Hence, <strong xss=removed>Sports Marketing</strong> is taught as a different subject in marketing. This marketing requires an understanding of sports and how they function as well along with the understanding of core subject. The various things taught during <strong xss=removed>Sports Marketing</strong> are identifying key issues in the current sports marketing environment. The subject explains and evaluates how sports can be used as a platform in the marketing of non-sport products and predict the effectiveness of the decisions made in marketing spectator sports; considering the impacts to both the live audience and the media-based audience.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/16720710-abstract-word-cloud-for-sports-marketing-with-rel.jpg\" alt=\"\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</span></strong><span xss=removed> has come up with <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong> to help out students with <strong xss=removed>Sports Marketing</strong>. Our online classes are light so that they can be managed with the regular classes and activities. The course has been designed by our panel of experts in a way that the subject is simplified and the subject becomes easy to understand.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Various topics covered under our online classes are <strong xss=removed>Introduction to Sports Marketing, Four Domains of Sports Marketing, Marketing through Sports, Marketing through Sports Using Theme-based Strategies, Traditional Sponsorship: Implementing an Alignment-based Strategy, Marketing of Non-sports Products via a Sports-sponsorship Platform: Three Special Forms of Sponsorship, The Marketing of Sports Products, Segmentation of the Sports Market, Product Decisions in Sports Marketing, Distribution Decisions and Facilities Management in Sports Marketing, Pricing Decisions in Sports Marketing,<span xss=removed>  </span>Developing a Promotional Strategy for the Marketing of Sports Products, Emerging Issues in Sports Marketing, Customer Relationship Management in the Business of Sports, Technology in Sports Marketing and Controversial Issues in Sports Marketing</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Our experts are highly qualified individuals with invaluable experience in their field of expertise. They understand the intricacies of the subject and hence have developed the online course accordingly. The sole purpose of the <strong xss=removed>online classes for Sports Marketing</strong> is to compensate for incomplete understanding and other doubts that creep in while studying. Our <strong xss=removed>Sports Marketing 4133 classes</strong> are available at a minimal price so that it is affordable for all. You can contact us via E-mail or a phone call to join our online classes. You can also visit the Take my online class to get more details on our website’s homepage.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>', 'COS0072', NULL, NULL);
