(233, 'SUB00228', 'Consumer Behavior 34320', 'consumer-behavior-34320', '', 'images_(2)2.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Consumer Behaviour</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed> (CB) is a field of study that aims to understand decision-making processes that consumers undertake when they identify the needs of, search for, evaluate, purchase, use, and dispose of products or services. This course specifically covers the sequences of decision-making processes that consumers go through, how individual differences in terms of social, cultural, economic, personal, and psychological factors affect their decision-making processes, and how consumers respond to marketing stimuli such as advertising campaigns or price discounts with various types of consumer responses. The knowledge of <strong xss=removed>Consumer Behaviour</strong> is expected to help marketing managers develop their successful marketing plans. Hence, an understanding of <strong xss=removed>Consumer Behaviour</strong> is hugely important from marketing perspective. With an objective of ensuring that students don’t struggle with subject and are able to smoothly understand the subject, <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong> for <strong xss=removed>Consumer Behaviour</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> <img src=\"../../assets/images/album/download25.jpg\" alt=\"\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Various topics covered under the online course are <strong xss=removed>Cross-cultural Variations in Consumer Behavior, Changing American Society: Values, Demographics and Social, Stratification, Subcultures and Family and Households, Group Influence on Consumer B