(235, 'SUB00230', 'Labor Relations Management 340 001', 'labor-relations-management-340-001', '', 'download_(2)1.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed>Labor Relations Management</strong> is a subject that deals with a very sensitive issue of <strong xss=removed>Labor Management</strong>. The subject discusses Labor relations concepts and the historical development of them, how labor relations and negotiations are influenced by environmental change, the importance of strategic planning and decision-making during labor relations and negotiations. The subject also aims to bring about an understanding of labor relations and their roles in the organization, the manager’s and union’s role during the labor relations process, the <strong xss=removed>importance of managerial and union involvement</strong> during the labor relations process and how labor relations are impacted by, and can also impact, organizational structure and its effects on organizational performance. Ultimately, the purpose is to prepare a student for <strong xss=removed>management of conflict</strong>, stress, and change in an effort to facilitate or inhibit labor relations in the future. Owing to the sensitivity and importance of the subject, <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong> for students.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/a4.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed>Some of the many topics covered in the online classes for Labor Relations Management are <strong xss=removed>Evolution of American Labor, Employment Law and Federal Agencies, Union Structure and Government, Unions: Member and Leader Attitudes, Behaviors, and Political Activities, Union Organizing Campaigns, Union Avoidance: Rationale, Strategies, and Practices, Environment for Bargaining, Wage and Benefit Issues in Bargaining, Nonwag