(238, 'SUB00233', 'Business Ethics and Sustainability ', 'business-ethics-and-sustainability', '', 'download43.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Any discussion of sustainable business practice needs to be set within a framework of understanding of business ethics. <strong xss=removed>Sustainability</strong> at the organisational level will be introduced for one or more reasons. It may be that organisation leaders have a deep commitment to sustainable business practice and this commitment is translated into the organisational mission, objectives, and goals. On the other hand, it may be that they recognise a market segment that is pro-sustainability and will seek out these businesses, or perhaps a growing concern amongst the general public for evidence of more sustainable business practice. <strong xss=removed>Business Ethics and Sustainability</strong> hence go hand in hand. It is important to understand both of them individually, their requirements and then consider them both together to understand the subjects. So that the students don’t trail behind in this all the more crucial subject, <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong> for students of <strong xss=removed>Business Ethics and Sustainability</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/download26.jpg\" alt=\"\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Some of the many topics covered under the online course are <strong xss=removed>A new framework for implementing corporate sustainability, Leadership, organizational culture, and strategy for corporate sustainability, Organizing for sustainability, Costing, capital investments, and the integration of sustainability risks, Performance measurement, evaluation and reward systems, The foundations for measuring social, environment