(240, 'SUB00235', 'Business Research Methods ', 'business-research-methods', '', 'download35.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Business Research Methods</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed> is a subject that will introduce you to Business research and explore how it differs from decision support systems and <strong>business intelligence systems</strong>. It further goes on to explore the trends affecting business research and the emerging hierarchy of research-based decision makers, the different types of research studies used in business, distinction between good business research and that which falls short of professional quality and the nature of the research process. These are very essential things that make the subject so important especially for the students who wish to do PhD and further research. Hence, to make this subject easily understandable, <strong>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong>online classes help</strong> for students. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed> <img src=\"../../assets/images/album/images_(1)10.jpg\" alt=\"\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Our online classes for <strong xss=removed>Business Research Methods</strong> cover a wide range of topics and themes such as <strong xss=removed>Research in Business, Ethics in Business Research, Thinking like a Researcher, The Research Process: An Overview, Clarifying the Research Question through, Secondary Data and Exploration, Qualitative Research, Observation Studies, Experiments, Surveys, Measurement, Measurement Scales, Questionnaires and Instruments, Crafting Effective Measurement, Questions, Sampling, Data Preparation and Description, Describing Data Statistically, Exploring, Displaying, and Examining Data, <span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></span>Hypothesis Testing, Measures of Association, Presenting Ins