(263, 'SUB00258', 'DSCI 205 Introduction to Business Statistics', 'dsci-205-introduction-to-business-statistics', '', 'images27.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed>Introduction to Business Statistics</span></strong><span xss=removed>, as the name suggests, dives into Statistical methods used in business research, analysis and decision making. Students are taught about preparation and presentation of data, frequency distributions, measures of central tendency and dispersion. Very importantly, you learn to draw statistical inference, regression and correlation. This is a pretty crucial subject for <strong xss=removed>Statistical studies</strong>. Hence, the <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced online classes help for students.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/a5.png\" alt=\"\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Amongst the various topics covered in this online course are<strong> Introduction to Business Statistics</strong></span><span xss=removed>, <strong>Displaying Descriptive Statistics</strong>, <strong>Calculating Descriptive Statistics</strong>, <strong>Introduction to Probabilities</strong>, <strong>Discrete Probability Distributions</strong>, <strong>Continuous Probability Distributions</strong>, <strong>Sampling and Sampling Distributions</strong>, <strong>Confidence Intervals</strong>, <strong>Hypothesis Testing for a Single Population</strong>, <strong>Hypothesis Tests Comparing Two Populations</strong>, <strong>Analysis of Variance (ANOVA) Procedures</strong>, <strong>Chi-Square Tests</strong>, <strong>Hypothesis Tests for the Population Variance, Correlation and Simple Linear Regression</strong>, <strong>Multiple Regression and Model Building</strong>, <strong>Forecasting</strong>, <strong>Decision Analysis</strong> and <strong>Nonparametric Statistics. </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=re