(270, 'SUB00265', 'College Algebra Math 1828 ', 'college-algebra-math-1828', '', 'download53.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed>Algebra</span></strong><span xss=removed> is one of the broad parts of <strong xss=removed>mathematics</strong>, together with <strong xss=removed>number theory, geometry and analysis</strong>. In its most general form, <strong xss=removed>Algebra</strong> is the study of <strong xss=removed>mathematical symbols</strong> and the rules for manipulating these symbols and is a unifying thread of almost all of mathematics. The subject encompasses everything from elementary equation solving to the study of abstractions such as groups, rings, and fields. The more basic parts of <strong xss=removed>Algebra</strong> are called <strong xss=removed>Elementary algebra</strong> and the more abstract parts are called <strong xss=removed>Abstract Algebra</strong> or <strong xss=removed>Modern Algebra. </strong>With an objective of helping students with this important subject of <strong xss=removed>Algebra</strong>, <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/images11.png\" alt=\"\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The various topics of Algebra covered in this online course are <strong xss=removed>Real Numbers, Properties of Real Numbers, Order on the Number Line, Absolute Value, Operations with Real Numbers, Interval Notation, Integers as Exponents, Scientific Notation, Order of Operations, Introduction to Polynomials, Add and Subtract Polynomials, Multiply Polynomial, Special Products of Binomials, Factor Polynomials; The FOIL Method, Factor Polynomials: The ac-Method, Special Factorizations, Equation-Solving Principles,  Inequality-Solving Principles, The Principle of Zero Products, The Principle of S