(274, 'SUB00269', 'Global Economics SEU ECN 500 ', 'global-economics-seu-ecn-500', '', 'download55.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>This subject applies and examines classical <strong xss=removed>economic knowledge of international trade and finance</strong> to inform decision making in the areas of business, management, and policy. Topics such as <strong xss=removed>classical trade theory, barriers to trade, regulatory policies, gross domestic product, and international banking</strong> are explored in this vast subject. With an objective of helping students with this all the more important subject, <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/images13.png\" alt=\"\"></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Some of the various topics covered in this online course are <strong xss=removed>The International Economy, Foundations of Modern Trade Theory, International Equilibrium, Trade Model Extensions and Applications, Tariffs, Nontariff Trade Barrier, Trade Regulations and Industrial Policies, Trade Policies for the Developing Nations, Regional Trade Arrangements, International Factor Movements and Multinational Enterprises, The Balance of Payments, Foreign Exchange, Exchange-Rate Determination, Balance-of-Payments Adjustments under Fixed Exchange Rates, Exchange-Rate Adjustments and the Balance of Payments, Exchange-Rate Systems, Macroeconomic Policy in an Open Economy and International Banking: Reserves, Debts, and Risk.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</span></strong><span xss=removed> hosts a panel of experts that specialize in a particular subject. These experts are then given the t