(309, 'SUB00304', 'the Introduction to Hydraulics and hydrology ', 'the-introduction-to-hydraulics-and-hydrology', '', 'download67.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed>Hydraulics</span></strong><span xss=removed> is a branch of science concerned with the practical applications of fluids, primarily liquids, in motion. It is related to <strong xss=removed>fluid mechanics</strong>, which in large part provides its theoretical foundation. <strong xss=removed>Hydraulics </strong>deals with such matters as the flow of liquids in pipes, rivers, and channels and their confinement by dams and tanks. Some of its principles apply also to gases, usually in cases in which variations in density are relatively small. Consequently, the scope of hydraulics extends to such mechanical devices as fans and gas turbines and to pneumatic control systems. <strong xss=removed>Hydraulics </strong>is quite a practical field and hence <strong xss=removed>Course Work Solutions</strong> has introduced <strong xss=removed>online classes help</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><img src=\"../../assets/images/album/a58.jpg\" alt=\"\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The various topics covered in this online course are <strong xss=removed>Hydraulics and Hydrology in Engineering, Fluid Mechanics, Fundamental Hydrostatics, Fundamental Hydrodynamics, Hydraulic Devices, Open Channel Hydraulics, Uniform Flow in Channels, Varied Flow in Channels, Culvert Hydraulics, Fundamental Hydrology, Runoff Calculations, Storm Sewer Design, Culvert Design, Storm water Detention and Detention Design, Monitoring and Modeling Hydrologic Systems, Rainfall-Runoff Estimation, Bernoulli’s equation and Friction Losses.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The course has bee