(334, 'SUB00329', 'Actuarial Science tutoring ', 'actuarial-science-tutoring', '', 'download77.png', '<p xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Actuarial Science tutoring </span></strong></p>\r\n<p xss=removed><strong xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\"> </span></strong></p>\r\n<p xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\" xss=removed>Actuarial science</span><span class=\"apple-converted-space\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\"> </span></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\">is a discipline which applies<span class=\"apple-converted-space\"> statistical and mathematical </span>methods to<span class=\"apple-converted-space\"> assess risks </span>in<span class=\"apple-converted-space\"> finance, insurance </span>and other professions and industries.<span class=\"apple-converted-space\"> </span> Actuarial science includes lots of interrelating subjects, like mathematics, statistics, probability, economics, finance, computer programming and financial economics. Actuaries<span class=\"apple-converted-space\"> </span>are the professionals who are experienced in this field via experience and education. The actuaries need to demonstrate their ability by passing series of thorough professional examinations. They are experts in evaluating financial impacts of upcoming uncertain events. They add worth by enabling individuals and businesses to make informed decision with a clearer vision of the probable range of financial outcome from different future event. They work in an extensive range of areas such as general insurance, life insurance, employee benefits and pensions, health insurance, investment, reinsurance companies, risk management and consultancies. An actuary needs to combine all the skills of an economist, statistician, and financier and utilize techniques of compound interest, probability, law, management and marketing to predict the outcomes of potential contingencies and design solution to lessen financial severity of these events.</span></p>\r\n<p xss=removed><span lang=\"EN-IN\"><img 